  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Established as a multiple bank in 1987, Banco Fibra S.A. (Fibra or the Bank) is one of the leading mid-sized Brazilian banks operating in the middle market segment. As of December 2009, Fibra posted total assets of R$11.8 billion and credit portfolio of R$5.5 billion, with net income of R$101.7 million. In March 2010, the Banks total assets reached R$8.5 billion, with credit portfolio of R$6.4 billion and net income totaled R$29.0 million in the first quarter of the year. 

The project involves the provision by IFC of a local currency indexed A Loan for an amount of up to $15 million. The project also includes a B Loan, for an amount of up to $75 million. The proceeds from the A and B Loan will be used by the Bank to expand its lending activities involving SME companies.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fibra has expertise in credit operations, particularly involving SME borrowers. The two major development impacts embedded in this project are: (i) expanding access to credit to underserved SME segment; and (ii) helping maintain a competitive environment in the concentrated Brazilian banking sector.</narrative>
  </description>
